### PALM COELBREN.

The palm Coelbren is that where twenty-four are cut on small dice, that
is, inasmuch as each die has six sides, and a letter on each side, there
will be on the four dice twenty-four letters, besides what may be
obtained otherwise, when the die is reversed, in order to show a
different letter.

Thus, <span id="img_15700"></span> ![](img/15700.jpg) and others, being
reversed, will make <span id="img_15701"></span> ![](img/15701.jpg), &c.
that is, a, â, e, ê, ng, c, d, y, y, m, turned upside down will make w,
ŵ, p, ff, ngh, d, dd, l, ll, w. By holding some of these in the palm of
the hand, and putting them together in the presence of a man of secrecy,
dumb conversation can be carried on.

